WORST OF THE WORST<br>
<br>
Welcome members of the Shattered Shield to the Worst of the Worst.<br>
<br>
Situation:  Lately there have been many competitions that have been run to decide who was the best character on the server and then in all EQ.  This is all good and well and our best to those people who win these events, they have worked hard for the most part to get where they are.  It is also well known that they are normally members of extremely large and powerful guilds.  The worst of the worst is out to change all this and the conduct is very simple.<br>
<br>
Mission: To conduct an arena battle of 1st level characters to find out who is the worst of the worst.<br>
<br>
Execution:<br>
<br>
What is required is that everyone in the guild who will be able to attend is to create a human warrior of the 1st level in the city of Freeport. This character can have any name as long as it ends in SS  IE: TreeceSS.  They can be Male or Female as your tastes dictate.  The statistics you chose for them are at your discression also.<br>
<br>
They are not to be equipped except for what items they start the game will and to ensure that character possess no buffs they will all be bound at the arena and debuffed before each battle.<br>
<br>
Items from the bank will be placed in random backpacks, the contents of the bags will vary from some very nice armour to a fishing pole it will be randomed.<br>
<br>
Two characters will be choosen and they will random a number and be allocated the corresponding back pack.  They then have 1 minute to sort their shit out before the battle begins.<br>
<br>
At the end of a battle all items are to be returned to the backpack and returned to the judge so they can be used again.<br>
<br>
This will be carried out until we find who is the worst of the worst.<br>
<br>
This is the first of such events.  Later we will do the same for other classes.<br>
<br>
A date and time to be announced shortly once the finer points are nutted out.<br>
<br>
It is planned to be held on a Saturday (USA) / Sunday (AUS) / Not Sure (Rest of the World).<br>
<br>
Please add any suggestions to this.<br>
